<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Encelia</i> <i>californica</i> and/or <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>cinereum</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Cleome</i> <i>isomeris</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>aurantiacus</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i>, <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i>, <i>Malacothamnus</i> <i>fasciculatus</i>, <i>Malosma</i> <i>laurina</i>, <i>Mirabilis</i> <i>laevis</i> var. <i>crassifolia</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>littoralis</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>leucophylla</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i> and <i>Sambucus</i> <i>nigra</i>. Emergent trees may be present, including <i>Juglans</i> <i>californica</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is variable. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Encelia californica</i> > 30% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Evens and San 2005, Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006, Klein and Evens 2005, Klein et al. 2010, Verdone and Evens 2010).</li>
		
		<li><i>Eriogonum cinereum</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub layer (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006, Verdone and Evens 2010).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Sunny, steep slopes that are often rocky or eroded. Soils develop from sandstone, shale, or volcanic  substrates.  </div>
</div>

        
